New Jersey investor David F. Bolgersaid he has delivered requests for a special meeting ofCleveland-Cliffs Inc &lt;CLF> shareholders representing more than25 pct of the total voting shares in the company.    Bolger, who heads a group that owns 6.4 pct ofCleveland-Cliff's outstanding stock, said he is seeking thespecial meeting to remove the current board of directors andelect his nominees.    The Bolger group had called for a special shareholdermeeting prior to the company's recent issuance of four mln newshares, Bolger said. Reuter&#3;